Defendant Frederick Lee Morrow in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Defendant Frederick Lee Morrow in custody.  
Benjamin Andrew Wesson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  PSI Report reviewed. Statements made by State, Denine J., defense, and defendant. 
 
AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  7 YEARS as to EACH COUNT, CONSECUTIVE to each other and any other time being served with credit for 0 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 5 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

The defendant IS NOT  eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF SUPERVISION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*No use of illegal controlled substances or alcohol;
*Cooperate with random urine screens;
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No contact with victims Rita M., Taylor P., Tiffany V., or Town Bank located at 140 S. 1st St. Milwaukee or North Shore Bank located at 5101 S. 76th St, Franklin;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment;
*Participate in vocational and/or educational training;
*Participate in Cognitive Intervention/Thinking program;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample if not previously done so- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs; 

The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amounts of $430.00 to North Shore Bank and $3323 to Town Bank.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations and restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  Appeal rights given.  The Court orders the defendant REMANDED into custody at this time.
